Yobe chief judge, Honourable Justice Garba Musa Nabaruma, has died on Monday. He died at the National Hospital, Abuja following a protracted illness. Nabaruma was the longest serving Chief Judge in Yobe State. He served for almost nine years in office until he died. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here His funeral session will take place on Tuesday according to Islamic rites. Yobe pioneer chief judge, Baâ€™aba, dies at 72 Bade emirate adviser dies at 93 Meet judges who are now traditional rulers